Coal India, HDFC Bank, Sun Pharmaceutical: India Stocks Preview

-- B y   P r a t i s h   N a r a y a n a n   a n d   R a j h k u m a r   K   S h a a w
-- 
2011-06-22T03:09:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-22/coal-india-hdfc-bank-sun-pharmaceutical-india-stocks-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in  India  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of the last close.  The Bombay Stock Exchange Sensitive Index, or Sensex, rose
53.67 points, or 0.3 percent, to 17,560.30. The S&P CNX Nifty
Index on the National Stock Exchange gained 0.3 percent to
5,275.85. The BSE 200 Index increased 0.1 percent to 2,182.50.
SGX S&P CNX Nifty Index futures for June delivery rose 0.6
percent to 5,308.5 as of 10:58 a.m. in  Singapore .  Coal India Ltd. (COAL)  : The world’s biggest coal
producer will cancel a tender for the development of two coal
blocks in  Mozambique  and will call for fresh bids by the end of
this month, the Wall Street Journal reported, citing an
unidentified company official. The shares fell 1.5 percent to
389.75 rupees.  HDFC Bank Ltd. (HDFCB)  : The third-biggest lender will
buy 1 percent stake in the Bombay Stock Exchange at 375 rupees a
share through the preferential allotment route, the Economic
Times reported without saying where it obtained the information
from. The shares added 1.2 percent to 2,325.55 rupees.  Indian Oil Corp. (IOCL IN): The nation’s biggest refiner
plans to raise $500 million by selling dollar bonds next month,
Finance Director P.K. Goyal said. The shares shed 0.7 percent to
323.50 rupees.  State Bank of India (SBIN)  : The country’s largest lender
expects its net interest margin for the year that began April 1
to be more than 3.5 percent, Chairman Pratip Chaudhuri said. The
shares slid 1.5 percent to 2,148.50 rupees.  Sun Pharmaceutical Industries Ltd. (SUNP)  : India’s
largest drugmaker by market value got the U.S. FDA approval for
its generic imitrex injection. The shares surged 2.4 percent to
488.2 rupees.  Timbor Home Ltd. (TIMB IN): The home furnishings maker will
commence trading after raising 232 million rupees in an initial
public offer at 63 rupees a share earlier this month. The offer
received 5.78 times demand.  To contact the reporter on this story:
